  "body_html": "<!DOCTYPE html\n  SYSTEM \"about:legacy-compat\">\n<html lang=\"en-us\" dir=\"ltr\"><head><title>Matches Operator</title><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"screen,projection\" href=\"/resource/css/style-v2.css\"><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"js/sap-strings.js\"></script></head><body class=\"en-us sap-light centered navigation-default enumeration-disabled\"><div id=\"d4h5-main-container\" class=\"container_12\" role=\"application\"><div id=\"d4h5-section-container\" class=\"grid_12\"><div id=\"d4h5-main-content\" class=\"grid_8 alpha omega\"><section><div class=\"page concept  - topic-topic concept-concept \" id=\"loio1a6842724a0e4a6b90b4c79513e382b6\"><h1 class=\"title topictitle1\">Matches Operator</h1><div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\"></p>\n<p class=\"p\">When defining validation rules and the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Precondition</span> part of\nsubstitution rules, you can use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Matches</span> comparison operator\nto match a string-type field value against a regular expression that is based on the\nPOSIX standard 1003.2. A regular expression is made up of literal characters and special\ncharacters following the syntax of regular expressions. It provides a concise and\nflexible means to represent a set of character strings.</p>\n<div class=\"p\">For example, you can define the following validation rule using the\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Matches</span> operator:<div class=\"table-wrapper tablenoborder\"><table summary=\"\" id=\"loio1a6842724a0e4a6b90b4c79513e382b6__table_jqd_4bj_yjb\" class=\"table\" data-table-id=\"table_jqd_4bj_yjb\" frame=\"border\" border=\"1\" rules=\"all\"><colgroup><col width=\"25%\"><col width=\"25%\"><col width=\"25%\"><col width=\"25%\"></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\" style=\"text-align:left;\">\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<th class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" id=\"d15535e73\"><p>Section</p></th>\n<th class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" id=\"d15535e76\"><p>Field</p></th>\n<th class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" id=\"d15535e79\"><p>Operator</p></th>\n<th class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" id=\"d15535e82\"><p>Value (Regular Expression)</p></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e73 \"><p><span class=\"ph emphasis emphasis\">Precondition</span></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e76 \"><p><span class=\"ph sap-technical-name sap-technical-name\">ProjectExternalId</span></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e79 \"><p><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Matches</span></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e82 \"><p><span class=\"ph sap-technical-name sap-technical-name\">12345.*</span></p></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e73 \"><p><span class=\"ph emphasis emphasis\">Validation</span></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e76 \"><p><span class=\"ph sap-technical-name sap-technical-name\">CostCenter</span></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e79 \"><p><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Matches</span></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\" headers=\"d15535e82 \"><p><span class=\"ph sap-technical-name sap-technical-name\">[A-Z][A-Z][[:digit:]]*999999</span></p></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">When a project ID starts with 12345, the rule requires that the cost center value starts\nwith two capital letters and be followed by a number that ends with 999999.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information about how to write regular expressions, see <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://help.sap.com/doc/abapdocu_750_index_htm/7.50/en-US/abenregex_syntax.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" alt=\"https://help.sap.com/doc/abapdocu_750_index_htm/7.50/en-US/abenregex_syntax.htm\" title=\"https://help.sap.com/doc/abapdocu_750_index_htm/7.50/en-US/abenregex_syntax.htm\">Syntax of Regular Expressions</a>.</p>\n</div></div></section><div class=\"clear\"></div>\n</div></div></div></body></html>"
}